version_description: Cited that this was the cover version of Johnoy Danao.
There are some mistakes in the chorus of the song and it's really misleading to play a wrong version so I improved it.
This is the simplified or easy version for beginners.
I demonstrate the finger picking pattern, which overlays on the lyrics throughout the song, but also placed the corresponding chords where they would fit in each verse and chorus. No capo.
This was the chord arrangement I put together based on the music video. You really have to listen to the song to see where the chord changes are.
This is the acoustic version. One guitar, tambourine, two voices.
There's no other tab, and many really really like this song, so it's nice to have a tab of it on here. The song is from X Ambassadors' album VHS 2.0.
Pretty accurate chords. More than 4 chords provided.
This is a simple version that sounds nice with the recorded version. Listen to recorded version for strumming pattern.
This is the first version on Ultimate Guitar as of yet plus no capo is required for this version.
